cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.CE, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is likely because the paper discusses the impact of ACC/CACC on vehicle flow and intersection throughput, which involves multiple agents (i.e. vehicles) interacting with each other. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely because the paper analyzes different car following models and their impact on intersection throughput, which involves control of vehicle dynamics. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possibility because ACC/CACC systems rely on information exchange between vehicles to coordinate their movements. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possibility because the paper uses SUMO simulation to evaluate the impact of ACC/CACC on a real-world road network. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possibility because ACC/CACC systems involve intelligent decision-making by vehicles to adjust their speed and maintain safe distances from other vehicles.
